Privacy Policy for KoiChi

Effective Date: April 6, 2026

KoiChi (“the app”) is a simple interactive experience designed to provide a relaxing environment. This Privacy Policy explains how information is handled when you use the app.

1. Information We Collect

KoiChi does not directly collect personal information such as names, email addresses, or contact details.

However, the app uses third-party services that may collect certain information automatically.

2. Third-Party Services

KoiChi uses Google AdMob to display advertisements and enable optional features (such as unlocking night mode through rewarded ads).

AdMob may collect and process data including:

Device identifiers (such as Advertising ID)
IP address
Device information (model, OS version)
App interaction data
Diagnostic information (crash reports, performance data)

This data is used to:

Provide and improve ads
Prevent fraud
Measure ad performance

For more information, please see:
https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads

3. Data Usage

Any data collected by third-party services is used for:

Serving advertisements
Improving app performance and stability
Analytics and reporting

KoiChi does not sell or share personal data independently.

4. Data Security

Data transmitted by third-party services is encrypted using standard industry practices (such as HTTPS).

5. User Control

Users can manage their ad preferences or opt out of personalized advertising through their device settings:

Android: Settings → Google → Ads → “Opt out of Ads Personalization”
6. Children’s Privacy

KoiChi is not specifically directed toward children under the age of 13. The app does not knowingly collect personal information from children.

7. Changes to This Policy

This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. Any changes will be reflected on this page.

8. Contact

If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, you can contact:

